{{Politics of Ethiopia}}
The '''All-Amhara People's Organization''' is an ethnic based political party in Ethiopia, whose leader was the late [[Asrat Woldeyes]].

At the last [[legislative]] [[Ethiopian general elections, 2005|elections]], 15 May 2005, the party was part of the [[United Ethiopian Democratic Forces]], that won 52 out of 527 seats in the [[Council of People's Representatives]].

